                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/46274",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dubbeltje",
                        "name": "dubbeltje",
                        "displayName": "Jigal Sanders",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hello, \r\n\r\nI also have trouble with this. \r\nI created a controller plugin:\r\n\r\npublic function preDispatch(Zend_Controller_Request_Abstract $request)\r\n{\r\n        $ajaxContextSwitch = Zend_Controller_Action_HelperBroker::getStaticHelper('AjaxContext');\r\n        $ajaxContextSwitch->setDefaultContext('json');\r\n        $ajaxContextSwitch->addActionContext('output','json');\r\n        $ajaxContextSwitch->initContext();\r\n}\r\n\r\nBut even though i get an error that my view script cannot be found.\r\n\r\nThis is the url i use:\r\n\r\n'\/user\/save-adres\/format=json'",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dubbeltje",
                        "name": "dubbeltje",
                        "displayName": "Jigal Sanders",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-05-01T09:55:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-05-01T09:55:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/46400",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bountin",
                        "name": "bountin",
                        "displayName": "Martin Prebio",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nI encountered a similar problem today and my solution\/my fault was that the action names are not normalized and therefore case-sensitive.\r\n\r\nI called http:\/\/XXX\/Auth\/Login-Mobile\/format\/json\/?format=json (Double parameter format to be sure that the format is found by the ContextSwitch Helper).\r\n{code}$contextSwitch->addActionContext('login-mobile', 'json'){code} didn't work but {code}$contextSwitch->addActionContext('Login-Mobile', 'json'){code} did. If I call ...\/login-mobile\/... the first ActionContext worked but the second didn't.\r\n\r\nAs a result I would recommend to normalize the ActionContext names to prevent this phenomenon like the action method names or the view script path names.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bountin",
                        "name": "bountin",
                        "displayName": "Martin Prebio",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-05-05T12:40:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-05-05T12:40:44.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
